📝 01Blog

A fullstack social blogging platform where students can share their learning journey, interact with posts, follow other users, and report inappropriate content.
Built with Spring Boot (backend) and Angular (frontend).

🚀 Overview

01Blog is a social platform designed for students to:

Publish learning posts (text + media)
Follow other users
Like and comment on posts
Receive notifications
Report inappropriate content
Admins can moderate users, posts, and reports
🧱 Tech Stack

Backend
Java 17+
Spring Boot
Spring Security (JWT)
Spring Data JPA
PostgreSQL / MySQL
Frontend
Angular
Angular Material
RxJS
TypeScript
Tools
Maven
Node.js
Git & GitHub

📦 Features

🔐 Authentication

User registration & login
JWT-based authentication
Role-based access control (USER / ADMIN)
Secure endpoints using Spring Security
👤 User System
Public user profiles ("blocks")
View other users' profiles
Subscribe / unsubscribe to users
Get notified of new posts from followed users
📝 Posts
Create / edit / delete posts
Text + image/video support
Timestamp on each post
Like and comment system
Real-time or refresh-based updates
🔔 Notifications
Notifications for:
New posts from subscribed users
Interactions (likes/comments)
Mark as read/unread
Notification center UI
🚨 Reports System
Users can report:
Posts
Profiles
Each report includes:
Reason
Timestamp
Reports are:
Stored in database
Visible only to admins
🛡️ Admin Panel

Admins can:

View all users
Manage posts (delete / hide)
Handle reports
Ban or delete users
Moderate platform content

All admin routes are protected with role-based access.

🎨 Frontend Features
Responsive UI (Angular Material / Bootstrap)
Home feed (subscribed users posts)
Profile pages
Post creation with media preview
Like & comment system
Report modal/dialog
Admin dashboard UI
🔐 Security
JWT authentication
Password encryption (BCrypt)
Role-based route protection
Admin-only endpoints secured
🗄️ Database

Relational database structure includes:

Users
Posts
Comments
Likes
Subscriptions
Reports
Notifications
📁 Project Structure
Backend
backend/
 ├── controllers/
 ├── services/
 ├── repositories/
 ├── models/
 ├── security/
 └── config/
Frontend
frontend/
 ├── src/app/
 │   ├── components/
 │   ├── services/
 │   ├── pages/
 │   └── guards/
⚙️ Installation & Run
Backend (Spring Boot)
cd backend
./mvnw spring-boot:run
Frontend (Angular)
cd frontend
npm install
ng serve
🌐 Environment Variables
Backend (application.properties)
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/01blog
spring.datasource.username=your_user
spring.datasource.password=your_password

jwt.secret=your_secret_key
🧪 Testing (optional)
./mvnw test
📌 Constraints
JWT authentication required
Role-based access control enforced
No code generation tools (JHipster not allowed)
Media stored locally or cloud (AWS S3 optional)
All admin routes protected
🌟 Bonus Features
WebSockets (real-time notifications/comments)
Infinite scroll feed
Dark mode
Admin analytics dashboard
Markdown support for posts

👨‍💻 Author

Built by Jaouhar Youssef as a fullstack learning project 🚀



# Docker commands


set -e

echo "📦 Installing Docker (rootless)..."

# Download and install Docker rootless
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com/rootless | sh

echo "✅ Docker rootless installed."

# Run rootless setup, skip iptables check, continue on error
echo "⚙️ Running dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh with --skip-iptables..."
~/bin/dockerd-rootless-setuptool.sh install --skip-iptables || echo "⚠️ Skipping setup tool errors."

# Set up environment variables
echo "⚙️ Setting up environment variables..."

echo 'export PATH=$HOME/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.zshrc
echo 'export DOCKER_HOST=unix://$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/docker.sock' >> ~/.zshrc
export PATH=$HOME/bin:$PATH
export DOCKER_HOST=unix://$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/docker.sock

echo "✅ Environment configured."

# Start the rootless Docker daemon in background
echo "🚀 Starting Docker daemon (rootless) in background..."
nohup dockerd-rootless.sh > ~/docker-rootless.log 2>&1 &

echo "✅ Docker daemon started in background (log: ~/docker-rootless.log)"

# Optional: install Docker Compose v2
echo "📦 Installing Docker Compose v2..."
mkdir -p ~/.docker/cli-plugins
curl -SL https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/v2.26.1/docker-compose-linux-x86_64 \
  -o ~/.docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose
chmod +x ~/.docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose

echo 'export PATH=$HOME/.docker/cli-plugins:$PATH' >> ~/.zshrc
export PATH=$HOME/.docker/cli-plugins:$PATH

echo "✅ Docker Compose installed."

# Verify installation
echo "🔍 Verifying installation..."
docker --version || echo "⚠️ Docker not found in PATH yet."
docker compose version || echo "⚠️ Docker Compose not found in PATH yet."

echo ""
echo "✅ All done! Run 'source ~/.zshrc' or restart your terminal to apply environment changes."



# docker
docker pull postgres
docker run --name blog-postgres -e POSTGRES_USER=postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres -e POSTGRES_DB=blogdb -p 5432:5432 -d postgres
docker ps
docker stop blog-postgres
docker start blog-postgres
docker exec -it blog-postgres psql -U postgres -d blogdb



# Spring Boot backend commands
cd backend-project-folder
mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run
./mvnw spring-boot:run


# Angular frontend commands
npm install @angular/cli
npx ng new my-app        # if not created yet
cd my-app
npm install
npm install baseline-browser-mapping@latest --save-dev
npx ng serve





src/main/java/com/
├── config/       ← Spring configs & initializers
├── controller/   ← REST endpoints (AuthController)
├── entity/       ← User, Post, Comment entities
├── repository/   ← JpaRepository interfaces
├── service/      ← AuthService, PostService (business logic)
├── security/     ← JwtUtil, JwtFilter, etc.
├── util/         ← Response class, helper classes